  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Renal failure and high plasmatic level of urea have been associated with an increased risk of
      hemorrhage in surgical patients. There is only sparse data on the impact of renal replacement
      therapy on homeostatic parameters. The aim of this study is to describe potential changes in
      homeostatic parameters before and after renal replacement therapy.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
